The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Archers to benefit
                                                                                                                       7                                      Archers to benefit
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The Archery Association of India (AAI) has inked a sponsorship deal for three years with the Sahara India Pariwar which will immensely benefit upcoming archers who would represent India in major events like the World Cup, Asian Games, Commonwealth Games and the London Olympics.         
	The sponsors will be paying Rs 2.40 crore (Rs 80 lakh per year) over three years. Each year, the AAI will spend Rs 50 lakh on players equipment and exposure tours while Rs 30 lakh will be distributed among talented archers so that they can buy equipment.         
	Saharas head of corporate communications, Abhijit Sarkar, distributed cheques worh Rs 30 lakh among 24 archers. Jayanta Talukdar received Rs 2.5 lakh while Mangal Singh Champia, Tarundeep Rai and Rahul Banerjee each received Rs 1.5 lakh.         
	Veteran Dola Banerjee was presented with a cheque for Rs 1.5 lakh while Cadet World Champion Deepika Kumari was richer by Rs 2 lakh.         
	Sahara also informed they have a plan to identify the top 15-20 sportspersons in each and every Olympic category and provide them with all possible financial help till the London Olympics.         
	One such plan has been to upgrade the facilities at the Bhiwani boxing club which has produced champions like Vijender Singh, Akhil Kumar.                                                                                                                     
